{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"alias":"compentant-briny-bat","description":"Observed 2026-07-10 during the adept-hedge-stain epic close-out: `rebar fsck` from current main (0.7.1, post-change-462) reports 14 issues — MISSING_CREATE on 9fa4-e87a-a5f0-4b7c and 13 ORPHAN_EVENT ('pre-snapshot event not captured in source_event_uuids') — while also WARNing the store contains ENQUEUE_ENRICH events newer than the running binary (written by a concurrent session on unmerged code) and 'ensures: 0/5 applied'.\n\nBand-A (A3) remediation had previously driven the live store to fsck-zero, so either (a) these are false positives from binary/store version skew (the older binary cannot interpret the newer events' effects, so replay bookkeeping looks orphaned), or (b) a genuine regression was introduced by post-A3 write activity. Do NOT run `rebar fsck --repair` from an older binary against the newer store — upgrade first (per fsck's own WARN: reconcile hosts upgrade first).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] After the ENQUEUE_ENRICH-introducing change merges to main, re-run `rebar fsck` from that binary against the live store and record the counts on this ticket.\n- [ ] If findings persist: classify each (version-skew artifact vs real orphan), and remediate real ones via the A3 tooling (`fsck --repair`, no-in-flight-pass check honored).\n- [ ] If findings clear: note the false-positive mechanism here and close; consider a follow-up so fsck labels skew-suspect findings when unknown-newer event types are present.\n- [ ] `ensures` converged (5/5 applied) via `rebar fsck --repair` run from the current binary.","id":"8c4f-b81c-98ca-45b9","parent_id":"","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"task","title":"Re-audit live-store fsck once ENQUEUE_ENRICH-era code lands: 13 ORPHAN_EVENT + 1 MISSING_CREATE reported by main's binary against a newer store"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783657478873148001,"uuid":"acb8530b-0dc3-45a5-916e-00986ad